### ============================
### Unknown JSON fields (demo)
### ============================
### Companion to the blog post:
### "Extra fields, ignored or not: unknown JSON properties in the MicroProfile REST Client"
###
### This endpoint deliberately returns SIX fields. A client mapping the response
### onto a three-field DTO keeps id/name/capacity and must ignore the rest -
### whether it does so depends on the JSON provider (JSON-B ignores by default,
### stock Jackson throws). See the Ch7_UnknownFieldsTest unit test for the proof.

### Get an over-stuffed room payload (id, name, capacity, building, floor, accessibility)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/unknown-fields/room-7
Accept: application/json

